com.esri.mo2.map.core
Interface ElementContainer

All Superinterfaces:
Searchable, Selectable
All Known Subinterfaces:
FeatureGraphicsLayer, GraphicsLayer, Layout
All Known Implementing Classes:
BaseFeatureGraphicsLayer, BaseGraphicsLayer, BaseLayout, PageLayout
public interface ElementContainer
extends Selectable, Searchable

An ElementContainer is a kind of container that manipulate Element objects added to it. It consists of functions to add element to it, remove element from it, select and search subset of the elements it contained. The elements added to container also have a z order and the container provides the capability to find out the z-order, and change the z-order for a given element.

addElement

public SelectionSet addElement(Element element,
                               int zorder)
Adds a graphic element with immediate z-order value specified. Z-order is a "hint" for where to place the Element in the z-order hierarchy and if <= 0 will be placed at the bottom of the z-order (will be drawn first). If zorder >= size() then the Element will be placed at the top of z-order, i.e. will be drawn last.

Parameters:
element - the graphic element
zorder - the initial z-order of the Element
Returns:
a SelectionSet identifying the element just added
See Also:
addElement(Element)
